    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2019-12-06</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-05-12T16:46:01Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Diversifying by Investing in Educators and Students to Improve Outcomes For Youth Act or the Diversify Act</strong></p> <p>This bill increases the maximum grant award under&nbsp;the&nbsp;Teacher Education Assistance for College and Higher Education (TEACH) Grant Program. The TEACH program awards grants to college students who plan to teach in low-income areas. </p> <p>The bill also exempts the TEACH program from sequestration, which is a process of automatic, usually across-the-board spending reductions under which budgetary resources are permanently cancelled to enforce specific budget policy goals. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
